  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      HYPOTHESIS AND SAMPLE SIZE The tumor delineated by FDG-PET is significantly different from
      the delineation achieved by MR T1 contrast weighted images in glioblastoma; expecting a
      standard error of 12.5 % (a confidence interval of 25%), with a confidence level set at 95%,
      a sample size of 15 patients would be accrued in the study.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
